a. Ensure adequate allocation of at least five percent (5%) of the total budget appropriations for priority programs, projects and activities that address gender issues or women’s concerns;

b. Direct the assigned GAD Focal Person to submit the Annual GAD Plan to the DILG Regional Office, as appropriate, for review and approval. Likewise submit the reviewed Annual GAD Plan and Annual GAD Accomplishment Report to the Audit Team as prescribed under COA Circular No. 2014-001 dated March 18, 2014.
